				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1755052">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							I believe you're confusing access to the public with employment law.  The Federal government has carved out exemptions from certain laws, such as anti-trust, in the realm of the large national sports franchises.  The NFL is exempt from the employment provisions of the ADA.  But the stadia have to be wheelchair accessible, so they have boxes reserved specifically for disabled persons.  Same with the NHL, the local Sharks Arena (locally called &quot;The Shark Tank&quot;) has at least one box available to disabled persons and their helpers.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
