				<div class="message">If a player could do that with their disability, they would be on the field.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Hence Jim Abbot. <br />
<br />
I think the issue facing games, along with Movies, books and music is that they're typically about &quot;enjoyment&quot; rather than &quot;necessity&quot;. <br />
<br />
A disabled person may not be able to necessarily &quot;enjoy&quot; a certain game as much as someone without a disability, but &quot;enjoyment&quot; is so subjective I don't think it can be reasonably regulated.
						</blockquote>
