				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Should online games allow use of assistive technologies for the handicapped?
				</h2>
				

						
						
							
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1755156">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Yaxa</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1755142#post1755142" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">There actually was a court case a few years back.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.arentfox.com/publications/index.cfm?fa=legalUpdateDisp&amp;content_id=2422" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Americans with Disabilities Act Does Not Require Video Game Manufacturer to Modify its Products</a></div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>That was a consumer plaintiff, I'm betting that if a disabled Sony employee had lost significant opportunities in the Quality Control department that they'd have to at least make reasonable accommodations so he or she could perform as a Quality Control department employee.<br />
 <br />
Perhaps that's another reason why so much production has fled overseas, companies trying to evade employer responsibilities under the ADA, even though accommodation isn't very expensive if it's always thought of and planned for in advance.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
